<Layout title="Career">
  <Container>
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center">Digital Marketing Manager</h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-10 mx-auto max-w-4xl mt-16">
      <div class="text-slate-700">
        <!-- <h2 class="font-medium text-2xl text-gray-800">Contact Nerd's House</h2>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-500 mt-3">
          Have something to say? We are here to help. Fill up the form or send
          email or call phone.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-5"></div> -->

        <p class="mb-4 text-sm">
          We're on the lookout for a passionate Digital Marketing Manager to
          take our online presence to new heights!
        </p>

        <p class="mb-4 text-sm">Responsibilities:</p>

        <ul class="list-disc text-sm font-light pl-8 mb-4">
          <li>
            <strong>Develop and implement digital marketing strategies:</strong>
            Create comprehensive digital marketing strategies aligned with the company's
            goals and target audience. This includes identifying target markets,
            competitor analysis, keyword research, and determining appropriate marketing
            channels.
          </li>

          <li>
            <strong>Website optimization:</strong> Ensure the company's website is
            optimized for search engines (SEO). Conduct keyword research, optimize
            meta tags, improve website structure, and work on increasing organic
            traffic and search engine rankings.
          </li>

          <li>
            <strong>Content marketing:</strong> Plan and execute a content marketing
            strategy to increase brand awareness and engage the target audience.
            Create compelling and informative content such as blog posts, case studies,
            whitepapers, and video tutorials related to WordPress and the company's
            products.
          </li>

          <li>
            <strong>Social media management:</strong> Manage and grow the company's
            presence on social media platforms such as Facebook, Twitter, LinkedIn,
            and Instagram. Develop engaging content, run social media campaigns,
            interact with followers, and use social listening tools to monitor brand
            mentions and customer feedback.
          </li>

          <li>
            <strong>Email marketing:</strong> Develop and execute email marketing
            campaigns to nurture leads and engage with existing customers. Create
            targeted email lists, design appealing newsletters, and analyze campaign
            performance using metrics such as open rates, click-through rates, and
            conversions.
          </li>

          <li>
            <strong>Paid advertising:</strong> Plan and execute paid advertising
            campaigns using platforms like Google Ads, Facebook Ads, and LinkedIn
            Ads. Monitor and optimize campaign performance, track conversions, and
            ensure the highest possible return on investment (ROI).
          </li>

          <li>
            <strong>Analytics and reporting:</strong> Use tools like Google Analytics
            to track website performance, user behavior, and campaign effectiveness.
            Generate regular reports on key metrics and provide insights to improve
            marketing strategies and tactics.
          </li>

          <li>
            <strong>Collaborate with the development team:</strong> Work closely
            with the development team to understand new product features, updates,
            and releases. Collaborate on website improvements, landing page optimization,
            and ensuring smooth integration of marketing campaigns with the website
            and plugins.
          </li>

          <li>
            <strong>Market research:</strong> Stay updated on industry trends, emerging
            technologies, and competitor activities. Conduct market research to identify
            new opportunities, potential partnerships, and areas for growth.
          </li>

          <li>
            <strong>Customer relationship management:</strong> Build and maintain
            strong relationships with existing customers. Collect customer feedback,
            address queries and concerns, and identify opportunities for upselling
            or cross-selling the company's products.
          </li>

          <li>
            <strong>Conversion rate optimization (CRO):</strong> Continuously optimize
            website and landing pages to improve conversion rates. Conduct A/B testing,
            analyze user behavior, and implement changes to enhance user experience
            and drive more conversions.
          </li>

          <li>
            <strong>Training and knowledge sharing:</strong> Stay informed about
            the latest digital marketing trends, tools, and techniques. Share knowledge
            and best practices with the marketing team and other stakeholders within
            the company.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">Why Nerd's House?</h2>

        <p class="mb-4 text-sm">
          We have crafted our own culture and traditions in the past decade and
          the highlights are:
        </p>

        <ul class="list-disc text-sm font-light pl-8 mb-4">
          <li>Certified Great Place to Work</li>
          <li>International client exposure</li>
          <li>Best employee benefits in the industry</li>
          <li>Performance appraisal twice a year</li>
          <li>No micro-management</li>
          <li>Health care and other benefits</li>
          <li>Frequent fully paid meetups</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="mb-4 text-sm">
          So if you are looking for a fairyland to spread your wings without
          being stifled by the constraints of the usual corporate culture look
          no further. We are happy to welcome you to our family.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <JobApplicationForm />
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="text-center mt-8">
      <a
        href="/career"
        class="bg-gray-100 px-5 py-3 rounded-md hover:bg-gray-200 transition"
        >‚Üê Back to Career</a
      >
    </div>
  </Container>
</Layout>
